         <br><div id=head style="border-bottom: 3px dotted black; margin-bottom:3px; "></div><br>
      <div class= "main">
      <p>Getting involved makes a difference in peopleâ€™s lives that are affected by family homelessness. Research and experience demonstrate that homelessness causes severe trauma to children and youth, disrupting their relationships, putting their health and safety at risk, and hampering their development. Homeless children are more likely than other children to have physical and mental health problems, and experience hunger and malnutrition. Emotional distress, developmental delays, and decreased academic achievement are also more common in this population of children. Many of these children and youth experience deep poverty, instability and exposure to domestic violence before becoming homeless, and homelessness increases their vulnerability to additional trauma.
      </p>

      <div class="pic" align= "center"><img src="https://economicrt.org/wp-content/uploads/2005/09/2005_Estimated_Cost_to_End_Homelessness_Main_01-730x390.jpg" style="width:50%;"></div>
