         <br><div id=head style="border-bottom: 3px dotted black; margin-bottom:3px; "></div><br>
      <div class= "main">
      <p>Many factors can contribute to a person becoming homeless. These factors include (but are not limited to):</p>
      <li>Poverty</li>
      <li>Lack of affordable housing</li>
      <li>Lack of health care</li>
      <li>Job loss</li>
      <li>Mental illness</li>
      <li>Domestic violence</li>
      <li>Substance abuse</li>
      <br>
      <p>The National Alliance to End Homelessness states that there are 564,708 people experiencing homelessness on any given night in the US. 36,907 (6.38%) are children, 47,725 (8.33%) are veterans, and 269,991 (47.6%) are disabled and unable to work.</p>
      <br>
